
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    `google-chrome` yek barname browser baraye gardesh dar internet ast. Ba in dastoor, shoma mitavanid Chrome ra az terminal baz konid va URL-ha ya option-haye mokhtalef ra be aan pass bedahid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `google-chrome URL` --> 🌐 Baz kardane yek safhe web khass.
    🔹 `google-chrome --new-window URL` --> 🖼 Baz kardane URL dar yek panjere jadid.
    🔹 `google-chrome --incognito URL` --> 🕵️‍♀️ Baz kardane URL dar halate makhfi (Incognito).
    🔹 `google-chrome --version` --> ℹ️ Namayeshe version Google Chrome.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ google-chrome
    
    🔹 Baz kardane Google Chrome be soorate normal.

    $ google-chrome https://www.example.com
    
    🔹 Baz kardane safhe web https://www.example.com dar Google Chrome.

    $ google-chrome --new-window https://www.example.com
    
    🔹 Baz kardane safhe web https://www.example.com dar yek panjere jadid.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ google-chrome --version
    
    🔹 Namayeshe version Google Chrome nasb shode dar system. Mesal: `Google Chrome 114.0.5735.198`.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    `google-chrome` is a web browser application.  This command allows you to launch Chrome from the terminal and pass it specific URLs or options.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `google-chrome URL` --> 🌐 Open a specific web page.
    🔹 `google-chrome --new-window URL` --> 🖼 Open the URL in a new window.
    🔹 `google-chrome --incognito URL` --> 🕵️‍♀️ Open the URL in Incognito mode.
    🔹 `google-chrome --version` --> ℹ️ Display the Google Chrome version.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ google-chrome
    
    🔹 Launch Google Chrome normally.

    $ google-chrome https://www.example.com
    
    🔹 Open the web page https://www.example.com in Google Chrome.

    $ google-chrome --new-window https://www.example.com
    
    🔹 Open the web page https://www.example.com in a new window.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ google-chrome --version
    
    🔹 Displays the installed Google Chrome version. Example: `Google Chrome 114.0.5735.198`.
